from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

scaler = StandardScaler()
scaler.fit(train_data[['Visits', 'DayOfWeek', 'Month']])

train_data_scaled = scaler.transform(train_data[['Visits', 'DayOfWeek', 'Month']])
test_data_scaled = scaler.transform(test_data[['Visits', 'DayOfWeek', 'Month']])

In [39]:
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
import numpy as np

# Define a range of k values to test
k_values = [1, 3, 5, 7, 9]

# Initialize lists to store results
k_values_results = []
rmse_values = []

# Iterate over different values of k
for k in k_values:
    # Train the KNN model
    knn_model = KNeighborsRegressor(n_neighbors=k)
    knn_model.fit(train_data_scaled, train_data['Visits'])

    # Make predictions on the test set
    predictions = knn_model.predict(test_data_scaled)

    # Calculate RMSE
    rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(test_data['Visits'], predictions))

    # Store results
    k_values_results.append(k)
    rmse_values.append(rmse)

    # Print the result for the current k
    print(f'k={k}, RMSE={rmse}')

# Plot RMSE values for different k values
plt.plot(k_values_results, rmse_values, marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Number of Neighbors (k)')
plt.ylabel('Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)')
plt.title('RMSE for Different Values of k in KNN Forecasting')
plt.show()

k=1, RMSE=79.24161364670292
k=3, RMSE=80.29607250207981
k=5, RMSE=86.6617178074225
k=7, RMSE=91.06589525674013
k=9, RMSE=100.03748474401715

from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
import numpy as np

# Define a range of k values to test
k_values = [1, 3, 5, 7, 9]

# Plot true values
plt.plot(test_data.index, test_data['Visits'], label='True Values', marker='o')

# Iterate over different values of k
for k in k_values:
    # Train the KNN model
    knn_model = KNeighborsRegressor(n_neighbors=k)
    knn_model.fit(train_data_scaled, train_data['Visits'])

    # Make predictions on the test set
    predictions = knn_model.predict(test_data_scaled)

    # Plot predictions for the current k
    plt.plot(test_data.index, predictions, label=f'Predictions (k={k})', marker='x')

# Set plot labels and title
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Visits')
plt.title('KNN Forecasting: True Values vs Predictions for Different k')

# Display legend
plt.legend()

# Show the plot
plt.show()
